modules.description: This module defines the default configuration parameters for identifier generation, including the character set, minimum length, and blocked strings. It provides direct access to the default alphabet, minimum length value, and blocklist entries. These values are used to initialize and customize identifier encoding and decoding processes.

This module generates and decodes short, unique string identifiers from integer lists, supporting customization of the alphabet, minimum output length, and blocklisted strings. It enables tasks like URL shortening, ID obfuscation, and slug generation, with direct functions for encoding and decoding using custom or default parameters. The child module supplies default configuration values—such as the standard alphabet and minimum length—which can be modified or extended to influence identifier generation behavior. Together, they offer a streamlined interface for creating robust, collision-resistant string identifiers tailored to specific application needs.
